Planning and Designing
Plan the website structure and layout, keeping the user experience in mind.
Sketch a rough design on paper or using design tools like Figma, Sketch, or Adobe XD.

HTML and CSS
Start by creating the HTML markup for the website.
Use CSS to style the website and make it visually appealing.
Implement responsive design to make the website mobile-friendly.

JavaScript
Use JavaScript to add interactivity to the website.
Implement features such as product search, filtering, and sorting.
Add a shopping cart feature to enable users to purchase products.

JSON
Create a JSON file that contains information about the products, such as the name, price, description, and image URL.
Use JavaScript to fetch data from the JSON file and display the products on the website.

Payment Integration
Implement a payment gateway to enable users to pay for their purchases securely.

Testing and Deployment
Test the website thoroughly to ensure that it works as expected.
Deploy the website to a web server or a hosting service.
Some additional tips for creating a unique eCommerce store:

Use unique and high-quality product images.
Write compelling product descriptions that highlight the features and benefits of the products.
Implement user reviews and ratings to help users make informed purchase decisions.
Use personalized recommendations to suggest products that users are likely to be interested in.
Implement social media integration to enable users to share products with their friends and followers.